Okay, ladies and gents, there's going to be a few changes to the format of the main page at Gallops.  One of the major changes will be sections for both editorials and product reviews.<br>
<br>
I already have the first editorial ready, and will be posting it this afternoon.  However, I need a first review ASAP, and don't want everything to have my name on it.  Also, I'd like to be able to post at least one of each (editorial and review) per week.  That's where you guys need to help out.<br>
<br>
If you want to write an editorial, just make sure it has some relevance to the stuff Gallops sells somehow.  If you wanna rant about how writer X has ruined your favorite comic, that's cool.  If you wanna rant about how Jake is a liberal nincompoop, and should be sent to an Iraqi raperoom to get the proper view of the situation, well, that's not related.  We won't get into right or wrong, just related or not.  Just make sure that the editorial is mostly thought out (I'll handle proofreading for you) and is longer than a paragraph but shorter than a 12 page manifesto.  Please format your submissions as a MS Word file attached to an email, sent to me at *nathan@gallopsstuff.com* (take out the two *'s...they're in there so that spam trollers don't catch the address) with the subject line 'Editorial Submission'.<br>
<br>
If you want to do a review, then please do it on something that the store has (or should have) in stock.  No previews, please.  For example, Ted has very few of the Exalted books in, but they're released, and I intend to do a review for them sometime next week.  Try to review things Ted can sell to readers of your review, and try to promote things, not slam them.  Pretend that <u>you</u> have to worry about the store making money, and you should be in the right mindset.  If you wanna submit reviews, use the same length guidelines and process for editorials, but give the email the subject line 'Review Submission'.<br>
<br>
Don't worry about being able to write or not, this isn't English class.  I'll help you proofread, and sent back a copy with revision suggestions if its so bad we can't put it up.  You won't fail, and we're not looking for Pulitzer material here.  (You'll understand tonight, when you can see the first editorial.)<br>
<br>
There's plenty of opportunity here.  If you need something to jog your creative gears, here's a few suggestions, which you don't have to adhere to in any way:<br>
<br>
Jeremy - Let's see an editorial about the change in Magic cards' appearance that's coming up.  Let the world know if you like it, don't like it, don't give a shit, and tell them why.<br>
<br>
Ken or Wayne - You're both big Abberant fans, and Ken has bought and read more books than I can stomach to (damn news format).  Review it!  Tell us why the settings great, because I honestly don't have a clue.<br>
<br>
Gabe - We deserve an editorial on how GW gaming is different so close to the source.  Let us know the ways and how the hobby is better and worse over there in relation to your home turf.<br>
<br>
Barclay - Holy crap, man!  You can review games that most of us have never read, but you've played!  Or, you can promote those games you love but no one else plays using the reviews.  Shadowrun, Traveller, Warhammer Fantasy Roleplay, and shit I've never heard of...review them all!<br>
<br>
This isn't hard to do at all.  I knocked out a 3 page editorial last night in less than an hour, and as I might have stated already, <u>I'll do the proofreading, if you don't want to.</u>  Next time you've got a bit of spare time, think of something about your hobby or hobbies you'd like to talk about, and do it!  Ramble, hell, I don't care.  We're looking for content, not paying subscribers. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:#DC143C;font-size:small;">Bungabunga &lt;Heavy Hand&gt;<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->53 Troll Beastlord<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->&quot;Have Gator, will travel.&quot;<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
